olive oil
1 portion cauliflower
1 potato
1 carrot
20 g butter
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 bag Soffritto Mix
1 packet tomato paste
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
¾ cup water
1 sachet Middle Eastern Seasoning
1 bag green beans

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut cauliflower into small florets. Place
cauliflower in a baking dish, then drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender and brown around the edges,
15-20 minutes.

• Meanwhile, bring a medium saucepan of salted
water to the boil.
• Peel potato and carrot, then cut both into large
chunks.
• Cook potato and carrot in the boiling water until
easily pierced with a fork, 10-15 minutes.
• Drain and return to the pan.
• Add the butter and a good pinch of salt. Mash
until smooth. Cover to keep warm.
• Meanwhile, trim green beans and cut into thirds.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over high heat. Cook beef & pork mince,
breaking up with a spoon, until just browned,
3-4 minutes.
• Add soffritto mix and green beans and cook
until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add Middle Eastern seasoning and tomato
paste and cook, stirring, until fragrant,
1 minute.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add beef-style
stock powder and the water and cook, stirring,
until reduced, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a dash more water if the mince is dry!

• Preheat grill to high.
• To the baking dish with cauliflower, add mince
filling.
• Spread veggie mash over evenly, then grill until
golden, 5-10 minutes.

• Divide Middle Eastern beef, pork and cauliflower
pie with veggie mash topping between plates.
Enjoy!